<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-14T15:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1401" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1401">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.116/341</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of the American Board of Commissioners
                                for Foreign Missions</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BRJL1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Rev. James L. Barton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                            <gloss type="to">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Clifton Springs, N. Y.</hi></placeName>,
                                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1915-07-14T15:45:00-05:00" notBefore="1915-07-10T00:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received July
                                    14, 1915, 3:45 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Advices from different parts of Turkey report inhuman treatment of
                                Americans<note n="1" xml:id="d1401fn1">According to letter dated
                                July 22, this should read “Armenians” (File No. 367.116/345).</note>
                            by Turks. Cannot something be done to alleviate the horrors?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BRJL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">James L. Barton</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>